						<div class="postbody">The state of development tools coupled with the expertise needed to create games for the SNES pretty much guarantees it's a niche within a niche for homebrew development.<br /><br />We need both assembly gurus and amateur 3rd generation language capable homeworkers to create a thriving scene.<br /><br />Sadly, the last effort to lower the bar on SNES game development has been abandoned twice:<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.snesgamemaker.comeze.com/">http://www.snesgamemaker.comeze.com/</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Anyone with knowledge of the 65816 flavor of <a href="http://www.villehelin.com/wla.html" class="postlink">wla</a> could pick up the pieces and add functionality to it.  Rejuvenate the project and grow the homebrew community.</div>

