				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I'll look into the code.<br /><br />I want to know how you are assembling the code.  Is it just a bunch of .asm files being assembled to a ROM individually, or are they using &quot;includes.&quot;<br /><br /><br />Here's a question for others on this website.  Is there a &quot;correct&quot; way to use NMI interrupts?  In the last couple of projects I've been using an IRQ interrupt in the place of an NMI, because NMI interrupts could trigger late when the CPU is busy, causing a black bar to appear at the top of the screen, instead of the usual slowdown.  If you keep the NMI interrupt flag set, it can interrupt the CPU while it's not finished with a frame, causing glitches, unless you reserve a byte of memory to signal if the frame is finished or not.<br /><br />EDIT:  Your code RTL after it clears wram.  That would cause crashing, due to the stack being swiped out.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
